data.reasoningText:
Now I have a clear picture of the project. Let me plan the component tree and implement everything.

Component Tree:
```
ApplyPage                    (page — owns all form state, orchestrates steps)
├── StepIndicator            (shows step progress bar)
├── PersonalInfoStep         (step 1)
├── WorkHistoryStep          (step 2)
│   └── WorkEntryForm        (single work entry)
├── ReferencesStep           (step 3)
│   └── ReferenceForm        (single reference)
├── CoverLetterStep          (step 4)
└── ReviewStep               (step 5)


```

Now I'm setting up the project structure. I'll start by creating the data models and service interface, then build out all the components with their styling files. The main orchestrator page will live in the Pages folder, and I'll organize the sub-components in a dedicated JobApplication folder using the appropriate namespace.

For the form state, I need mutable classes to handle user input during the application process, then convert those to the immutable records when submitting. Let me start creating all the files now, batching the components together efficiently.

```

csharp
